1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,919
<i>Go! </i>[COUGHING]

2
00:00:03,002 --> 00:00:04,087
<i>Mommy! Mommy!</i>

3
00:00:04,170 --> 00:00:05,505
<i>Mommy, wake up!</i>

4
00:00:07,173 --> 00:00:08,717
<i>Help!</i>

5
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:10,510
<i>Honey!</i>
[MIKE GROANS IN PAIN]

6
00:00:10,593 --> 00:00:12,512
<i>Minnie? What happened to you?</i>

7
00:00:12,595 --> 00:00:14,305
<i>- Maddie…</i>
<i>- Where's Maddie?</i>

8
00:00:14,389 --> 00:00:16,808
<i>I don't know.</i>
<i>We were together just before.</i>

9
00:00:17,684 --> 00:00:19,769
<i>- Liam!</i>
<i>- Maddie!</i>

10
00:00:20,854 --> 00:00:21,730
[MADDIE WHIMPERS]

11
00:00:22,814 --> 00:00:23,857
[RUMBLING]

12
00:00:23,940 --> 00:00:24,983
[GROANS]

13
00:00:25,066 --> 00:00:29,070
<i>- Boss! Boss Emil!</i>
- [EMIL GROANS]

14
00:00:29,654 --> 00:00:31,906
<i>Boss! Boss!</i>

15
00:00:33,366 --> 00:00:34,284
[OFFICER] <i>Medic!</i>

16
00:00:36,369 --> 00:00:38,496
- [POLICE] <i>You can't go there, sir!</i>
- [OLSEN] <i>Liam!</i>

17
00:00:39,789 --> 00:00:42,167
<i>- He's with us! Liam! Liam!</i>
- [POLICE] <i>Medic!</i>

18
00:00:43,668 --> 00:00:44,961
[MEDIC] <i>Over here.</i>

19
00:00:48,923 --> 00:00:50,842
<i>- I'm going to look for Maddie!</i>
<i>- Stay here, please.</i>

20
00:00:50,925 --> 00:00:52,761
<i>- Hon, I'll go look for her.</i>
<i>- No!</i>

21
00:00:52,844 --> 00:00:53,928
<i>Mommy! Daddy!</i>

22
00:00:54,012 --> 00:00:55,180
<i>Maddie!</i>

23
00:00:56,639 --> 00:00:57,974
[MIKE AND MINNIE]
<i>Maddie.</i>

24
00:00:59,142 --> 00:01:00,643
<i>We need to go back for Papa!</i>

25
00:01:00,727 --> 00:01:03,730
<i>- He's gone. Boss Emil's gone.</i>
- [LENI]<i> No!</i>

26
00:01:03,813 --> 00:01:06,441
<i>He's buried under the building.</i>

27
00:01:06,524 --> 00:01:08,651
<i>We don't know where he could be.</i>

28
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:10,403
[GASPS]

29
00:01:19,537 --> 00:01:23,291
- [MINNIE CRYING]
- [MIKE PANTING]

30
00:01:28,713 --> 00:01:30,548
[OFFICER] <i>Lieutenant Areza, do you copy?</i>

31
00:01:32,300 --> 00:01:35,678
Check the area carefully,
including the sewage system.

32
00:01:35,762 --> 00:01:38,014
Focus on Marcelino Street.

33
00:01:38,097 --> 00:01:42,519
According to Engineer Mike,
the hostage takers will exit from there!

34
00:01:43,019 --> 00:01:48,316
[SIREN WAILING]

35
00:01:53,780 --> 00:02:00,120
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

36
00:02:03,248 --> 00:02:05,250
Positive, sir. They were here.

37
00:02:06,334 --> 00:02:08,002
Marcelino Street.

38
00:02:10,588 --> 00:02:14,342
[SIREN WAILING]

39
00:02:14,425 --> 00:02:17,220
[REPORTER 1] Lieutenant,
have the hostage takers been caught?

40
00:02:17,303 --> 00:02:18,805
Are they still inside?

41
00:02:18,888 --> 00:02:20,557
[REPORTER 2] Sir, has anyone died?

42
00:02:21,391 --> 00:02:24,727
We'll release an update
once we have all the information.

43
00:02:24,811 --> 00:02:25,770
Thank you.

44
00:02:25,854 --> 00:02:28,523
Sir, are there still people inside?

45
00:02:28,606 --> 00:02:32,277
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

46
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:34,654
It's better if you just go home.

47
00:02:34,737 --> 00:02:37,323
- We'll accompany you.
- [OLSEN] Where's Ma'am Greta?

48
00:02:37,991 --> 00:02:39,200
Did they find her or not?

49
00:02:39,284 --> 00:02:40,994
Did she make it out?

50
00:02:41,077 --> 00:02:43,413
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

51
00:02:43,496 --> 00:02:45,123
We're still looking for her.

52
00:02:47,208 --> 00:02:49,294
[OFFICER] <i>Lieutenant Areza, do you copy?</i>

53
00:02:50,128 --> 00:02:51,004
Go ahead.

54
00:02:51,671 --> 00:02:54,132
[OFFICER] <i>Sir, Emil Padua has been found.</i>

55
00:03:02,682 --> 00:03:08,980
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

56
00:03:23,953 --> 00:03:30,710
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

57
00:03:35,048 --> 00:03:37,133
Patient is male, in his sixties.

58
00:03:37,217 --> 00:03:39,093
Heavy smoke inhalation.

59
00:03:39,177 --> 00:03:42,096
Multiple wounds and second-degree burns.

60
00:03:42,805 --> 00:03:44,474
He's unconscious.

61
00:03:44,557 --> 00:03:48,269
We need to monitor his blood oxygen
and stabilize his breathing.

62
00:03:48,353 --> 00:03:50,271
- Copy.
- Doc, wait!

63
00:03:51,856 --> 00:03:53,274
Someone needs to go with us.

64
00:03:58,029 --> 00:03:59,113
Yes, sir.

65
00:03:59,197 --> 00:04:04,702
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

66
00:04:17,715 --> 00:04:23,805
[SIREN WAILING]

67
00:04:32,981 --> 00:04:38,987
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

68
00:05:11,936 --> 00:05:18,901
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

69
00:05:37,336 --> 00:05:38,671
Doc Jessie.

70
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:41,591
Ma'am Conney.

71
00:05:42,341 --> 00:05:43,926
What happened?

72
00:05:45,178 --> 00:05:49,849
We requested you be transferred here
to our hospital in Manila.

73
00:05:50,641 --> 00:05:52,310
You lost consciousness, Liam,

74
00:05:52,393 --> 00:05:55,188
after escaping from the St. John's fire.

75
00:05:55,897 --> 00:05:59,442
Your lungs were filled with smoke.

76
00:06:00,026 --> 00:06:03,196
You were severely dehydrated.

77
00:06:04,530 --> 00:06:06,074
You almost died, son.

78
00:06:09,368 --> 00:06:10,495
<i>Ma!</i>

79
00:06:10,578 --> 00:06:11,621
<i>Ma!</i>

80
00:06:11,704 --> 00:06:14,123
[PANTING] <i>Ma!</i>

81
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:18,669
[GRUNTING]

82
00:06:19,253 --> 00:06:20,713
[MADDIE] <i>Help!</i>

83
00:06:30,765 --> 00:06:32,975
<i>- Liam!</i>
<i>- Maddie!</i>

84
00:06:34,268 --> 00:06:35,645
<i>Ma!</i>

85
00:06:36,896 --> 00:06:38,022
<i>Ma!</i>

86
00:06:38,106 --> 00:06:40,942
[MADDIE CRYING]

87
00:06:41,025 --> 00:06:42,944
- [COUGHS]
- [MADDIE] <i>Mommy.</i>

88
00:06:43,027 --> 00:06:44,862
[MADDIE CRYING]

89
00:06:45,363 --> 00:06:46,781
<i>Medic!</i>

90
00:06:51,452 --> 00:06:53,996
- [OFFICER]<i> You can't go there, sir!</i>
<i>- Liam!</i>

91
00:06:56,749 --> 00:06:58,167
Where's Mama?

92
00:06:59,127 --> 00:07:00,294
Um…

93
00:07:01,003 --> 00:07:06,968
Liam, your mom wasn't among the casualties
found at St. John's,

94
00:07:07,051 --> 00:07:09,470
so she might still be alive.

95
00:07:10,054 --> 00:07:11,347
"Might"?

96
00:07:11,431 --> 00:07:14,058
The police are searching for her.

97
00:07:27,488 --> 00:07:34,454
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

98
00:07:49,802 --> 00:07:56,142
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

99
00:07:57,518 --> 00:07:58,895
[LIAM] What about Papa?

100
00:07:59,937 --> 00:08:02,815
Your papa is in custody.

101
00:08:02,899 --> 00:08:04,775
He's a person of interest too.

102
00:08:06,986 --> 00:08:12,241
We still can't believe that
your mom is allegedly involved.

103
00:08:12,325 --> 00:08:15,119
She's said to be the mastermind
behind the hostage taking.

104
00:08:15,745 --> 00:08:18,498
You know, that's also
what Captain Jacinto says.

105
00:08:19,165 --> 00:08:22,502
Liam, there's allegedly a video
proving your mom's involvement.

106
00:08:22,585 --> 00:08:26,714
Maybe Captain Jacinto
recorded it during their meeting.

107
00:08:26,797 --> 00:08:31,385
For safety, in case he needed leverage.

108
00:08:31,469 --> 00:08:34,430
But of course,
with all the deepfakes these days,

109
00:08:34,514 --> 00:08:38,351
we can't be sure
if that video's real, right?

110
00:08:38,434 --> 00:08:41,729
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

111
00:08:41,812 --> 00:08:43,105
Um…

112
00:08:44,774 --> 00:08:49,695
Liam, I hope you don't mind my asking.

113
00:08:50,488 --> 00:08:52,156
Do you know anything?

114
00:08:52,907 --> 00:08:55,701
Is it true your mom was involved?

115
00:08:55,785 --> 00:09:02,458
[MUSIC BECOMES DARK]

116
00:09:12,301 --> 00:09:13,636
I'm so sorry.

117
00:09:17,890 --> 00:09:19,600
But Papa wasn't involved.

118
00:09:20,309 --> 00:09:22,436
He had nothing to do with it.

119
00:09:27,525 --> 00:09:29,610
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

120
00:09:31,529 --> 00:09:35,366
If there's anyone who'd know
Greta Roja's whereabouts,

121
00:09:36,117 --> 00:09:37,702
that'd be you, Mr. Roja.

122
00:09:37,785 --> 00:09:43,457
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

123
00:09:45,376 --> 00:09:49,088
My client has already given you
a list of all his properties.

124
00:09:49,797 --> 00:09:52,550
Those are all the possible places
my wife could be hiding.

125
00:09:54,802 --> 00:09:56,721
Believe it or not,

126
00:09:57,888 --> 00:10:00,891
if I find out where my wife is hiding,

127
00:10:02,310 --> 00:10:07,064
I will surrender her to you myself.

128
00:10:07,148 --> 00:10:13,529
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

129
00:10:19,327 --> 00:10:20,745
[LIAM] <i>Why did you do this?</i>

130
00:10:22,663 --> 00:10:23,789
<i>Why?!</i>

131
00:10:23,873 --> 00:10:26,459
[GRETA CRYING] <i>Liam.</i>

132
00:10:26,542 --> 00:10:27,543
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

133
00:10:28,961 --> 00:10:31,964
<i>I was desperate. We're drowning in debt.</i>

134
00:10:33,215 --> 00:10:36,719
<i>Our family's flat-out broke.</i>
<i>I didn't know what to do.</i>

135
00:10:36,802 --> 00:10:40,014
<i>I had no choice.</i>
<i>That was all I could think of.</i>

136
00:10:40,097 --> 00:10:42,516
<i>Do you know how many died because of you?!</i>

137
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:45,603
<i>So many people died!</i>

138
00:10:45,686 --> 00:10:47,313
<i>This isn't about money, Ma!</i>

139
00:10:48,481 --> 00:10:52,234
<i>This is about lives!</i>
<i>Chief Ben's and our employees'!</i>

140
00:10:52,818 --> 00:10:55,363
[GRETA] <i>Liam, I don't want to go to jail.</i>

141
00:10:55,446 --> 00:10:57,615
<i>I don't want to go to jail.</i>
<i>I'm begging you!</i>

142
00:10:58,532 --> 00:11:00,201
<i>I'm begging you.</i>

143
00:11:00,284 --> 00:11:02,453
[GRETA CRYING]

144
00:11:02,536 --> 00:11:03,621
<i>Liam.</i>

145
00:11:05,539 --> 00:11:07,375
<i>Liam, I'm begging you.</i>

146
00:11:08,918 --> 00:11:10,670
<i>I don't want to go to jail.</i>

147
00:11:10,753 --> 00:11:13,714
[GRETA] <i>Have mercy on me.</i>

148
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:16,217
[GRETA CRYING]

149
00:11:19,553 --> 00:11:26,560
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

150
00:11:34,193 --> 00:11:36,987
[POLICE SIRENS BLARING]

151
00:11:41,534 --> 00:11:43,994
Shouldn't you be focusing more

152
00:11:44,078 --> 00:11:46,497
on catching Lucas Sebastian
and his associates?

153
00:11:48,374 --> 00:11:50,251
What if he threatens to kill my wife?

154
00:11:51,961 --> 00:11:53,170
Or my son?

155
00:11:53,254 --> 00:11:55,464
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

156
00:11:55,548 --> 00:11:59,635
What if they're already holding her
hostage right now, as we speak?

157
00:12:01,595 --> 00:12:04,765
A search operation
for the suspects is ongoing.

158
00:12:04,849 --> 00:12:07,518
A task force has been set up for that.

159
00:12:09,145 --> 00:12:11,063
Well, then, what do you need me for?

160
00:12:13,399 --> 00:12:15,025
If you don't have evidence,

161
00:12:15,776 --> 00:12:17,153
then you don't.

162
00:12:17,903 --> 00:12:20,739
If you're going to sue me, then sue me.

163
00:12:21,365 --> 00:12:22,700
I need to see my son.

164
00:12:23,325 --> 00:12:25,828
I need to see Liam, Lieutenant.

165
00:12:26,787 --> 00:12:28,372
I'm just reminding you.

166
00:12:29,832 --> 00:12:33,169
You're not allowed to go beyond
the legal detention period.

167
00:12:33,961 --> 00:12:35,796
If there is no case,

168
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:37,965
you will have to release my client.

169
00:12:38,048 --> 00:12:44,763
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

170
00:12:52,980 --> 00:12:59,778
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

171
00:13:07,703 --> 00:13:11,081
[POLICE SIRENS BLARING]

172
00:13:11,999 --> 00:13:17,755
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

173
00:13:26,847 --> 00:13:29,600
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

174
00:13:29,683 --> 00:13:30,809
[METAL LOCK SCRAPING]

175
00:13:34,772 --> 00:13:35,689
[METAL LOCK SCRAPING]

176
00:13:35,773 --> 00:13:39,860
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

177
00:13:39,944 --> 00:13:41,403
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

178
00:13:41,487 --> 00:13:42,821
[DOOR CREAKING OPEN]

179
00:13:42,905 --> 00:13:47,493
[SOFT FOOTSTEPS]

180
00:13:47,576 --> 00:13:54,542
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

181
00:14:02,466 --> 00:14:04,301
Search the area! Move!

182
00:14:04,385 --> 00:14:10,724
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

183
00:14:23,529 --> 00:14:30,452
[SOFT FOOTSTEPS]

184
00:14:30,536 --> 00:14:31,453
[DOOR CREAKING OPEN]

185
00:14:31,537 --> 00:14:38,377
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

186
00:14:42,339 --> 00:14:43,507
Sir, negative.

187
00:14:45,384 --> 00:14:51,265
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

188
00:15:07,406 --> 00:15:14,371
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

189
00:15:25,883 --> 00:15:28,636
<i>Authorities are still searching</i>
<i>for Greta Roja.</i>

190
00:15:28,719 --> 00:15:32,973
<i>Meanwhile, her husband, Magnus Roja,</i>

191
00:15:33,057 --> 00:15:35,851
<i>who is considered a person</i>
<i>of interest, is still detained.</i>

192
00:15:38,103 --> 00:15:43,609
[SOFT FOOTSTEPS]

193
00:16:00,376 --> 00:16:02,002
[GRETA CRYING]

194
00:16:02,086 --> 00:16:05,965
<i>I can't do this.</i>

195
00:16:06,048 --> 00:16:09,969
<i>Please! I'm begging you!</i>

196
00:16:10,052 --> 00:16:16,517
[GRETA CRYING]

197
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:18,644
<i>Don't you love me anymore?</i>

198
00:16:20,104 --> 00:16:27,027
[GRETA CRYING]

199
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:31,824
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

200
00:16:32,491 --> 00:16:36,328
<i>I'm turning you in to the police</i>
<i>because it's the right thing to do.</i>

201
00:16:38,372 --> 00:16:40,165
<i>That's how you raised me.</i>

202
00:16:40,249 --> 00:16:43,877
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

203
00:16:43,961 --> 00:16:45,713
<i>It's not that I don't love you.</i>

204
00:16:46,922 --> 00:16:48,841
[LIAM] <i>Ma! Turn yourself in.</i>

205
00:16:49,341 --> 00:16:50,718
<i>I'm begging you.</i>

206
00:16:50,801 --> 00:16:54,847
<i>Let's start over!</i>
<i>You, me, and your father.</i>

207
00:16:54,930 --> 00:16:56,557
<i>Let's run away.</i> [COUGHS]

208
00:16:56,640 --> 00:17:00,144
<i>Let's go somewhere no one knows about.</i>

209
00:17:01,228 --> 00:17:03,022
<i>Do you even hear yourself, Ma?!</i>

210
00:17:03,105 --> 00:17:05,524
<i>You want us to run away? All of us?</i>

211
00:17:05,607 --> 00:17:07,609
[LIAM] <i>Do you want us to be criminals?!</i>

212
00:17:13,449 --> 00:17:17,244
[REPORTER] <i>It's confirmed</i>
<i>that one of the suspects,</i>

213
00:17:17,327 --> 00:17:19,038
<i>Diosdado Menor, died from the fire.</i>

214
00:17:19,621 --> 00:17:23,000
<i>However, some of the suspects</i>
<i>have yet to be captured.</i>

215
00:17:23,083 --> 00:17:25,836
<i>These are Homer Sebastian, Gwen Zamora,</i>

216
00:17:25,919 --> 00:17:28,589
<i>Leni Padua, and Lucas Sebastian.</i>

217
00:17:28,672 --> 00:17:32,384
<i>Sebastian's wife, Mila Sebastian,</i>
<i>is now in custody.</i>

218
00:17:32,468 --> 00:17:35,888
<i>She was allegedly complicit</i>
<i>in the hostage taking.</i>

219
00:17:36,472 --> 00:17:40,559
<i>The leader of the group, Emil Padua,</i>
<i>is currently in critical condition.</i>

220
00:17:40,642 --> 00:17:44,605
<i>He is currently confined</i>
<i>in a hospital in Alicante.</i>

221
00:17:46,732 --> 00:17:53,489
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

222
00:17:54,406 --> 00:17:56,408
His vitals are stable, Doc.

223
00:17:56,492 --> 00:17:58,869
Continue oxygen sat every 15 minutes?

224
00:17:59,828 --> 00:18:00,913
Yes.

225
00:18:01,413 --> 00:18:05,751
Notify me if he shows any signs
of respiratory distress.

226
00:18:06,376 --> 00:18:07,419
Okay, Doc.

227
00:18:07,503 --> 00:18:10,672
[EKG BEEPING STEADILY]

228
00:18:10,756 --> 00:18:17,137
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

229
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:35,405
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

230
00:18:41,036 --> 00:18:42,830
[LUNA]<i> Why did you even volunteer?</i>

231
00:18:42,913 --> 00:18:45,582
<i>Why do you have to treat Emil Padua?</i>

232
00:18:45,666 --> 00:18:49,128
<i>Until all of them are caught,</i>
<i>we are not safe.</i>

233
00:18:49,211 --> 00:18:50,587
[AREZA] <i>I believe you are innocent.</i>

234
00:18:50,671 --> 00:18:52,131
[WOMAN] <i>Put the Rojas behind bars!</i>

235
00:18:52,214 --> 00:18:54,633
[PROTESTORS]
<i>Put the Rojas behind bars!</i>

236
00:18:54,716 --> 00:18:58,554
- [PROTESTOR 1] <i>They shouldn't be free!</i>
- [PROTESTOR 2]<i> Criminals!</i>

237
00:18:58,637 --> 00:19:01,140
[ICE] <i>Everything that happened</i>
<i>on the island made me realize</i>

238
00:19:01,223 --> 00:19:03,475
<i>how much I miss my mom.</i>

239
00:19:03,559 --> 00:19:05,394
<i>She almost lost me, Olsen.</i>

240
00:19:08,397 --> 00:19:11,150
<i>I can assure you, we're not hiding Mama.</i>

241
00:19:12,484 --> 00:19:14,736
<i>We also want justice for everyone.</i>

242
00:19:14,820 --> 00:19:18,073
<i>I really don't know</i>
<i>where Greta is to be found.</i>

243
00:19:18,157 --> 00:19:21,743
<i>I understand</i>
<i>where your loyalty is, Magnus.</i>

244
00:19:21,827 --> 00:19:23,954
<i>But what about my father?</i>

245
00:19:24,955 --> 00:19:27,958
<i>What about the people who suffered</i>
<i>because of your wife?</i>

246
00:19:29,001 --> 00:19:30,544
<i>Do you still have a conscience?</i>

247
00:19:39,928 --> 00:19:43,390
<i>If you truly care about us…</i>

248
00:19:45,934 --> 00:19:47,186
<i>about me…</i>

249
00:19:49,188 --> 00:19:51,607
<i>then give us peace.</i>

250
00:19:56,486 --> 00:19:58,488
[LUCAS] <i>The mission is not yet over.</i>

251
00:20:01,909 --> 00:20:03,493
<i>We need to get Mila!</i>

252
00:20:03,577 --> 00:20:04,953
<i>We'll get your father back, Leni.</i>

253
00:20:05,037 --> 00:20:07,206
<i>At what cost?</i>
<i>How many more are going to die?</i>

254
00:20:07,289 --> 00:20:10,042
<i>You're even putting Papa's life</i>
<i>on the line with your plan.</i>

255
00:20:10,125 --> 00:20:11,460
<i>You wouldn't understand.</i>

256
00:20:11,543 --> 00:20:14,296
<i>Fathers will never abandon their children.</i>

257
00:20:14,379 --> 00:20:16,006
<i>We don't leave them.</i>

258
00:20:16,089 --> 00:20:17,674
<i>What do you know about being a father?</i>

259
00:20:17,758 --> 00:20:20,677
<i>Isn't Olsen your son? What did you do?</i>

260
00:20:20,761 --> 00:20:26,725
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]
